{/* 1. About Me */}

About Me

{/* Now */}

Now

I’m currently pursuing an MPhil in Biotechnology at the University of Cambridge, focusing on the intersection of AI and biology. Specifically, I am looking at single-cell foundation models and using them for drug discovery. Whilst I have been here, I have been finally involving myself in AI safety, having spent the last few years lurking in this space. Through this, I was involved in MARS 2.0, the second edition of the MARS research program. I was incredibly lucky to research with a great team, where we investigated using {" "}Gradient Routing{" "} for circuit transplantation in transformer models. On top of this, I am a part of the AI Safety Committee here in Cambridge. I am also currently a baby VC fellow.

{/* Before */}

Before

I previously completed my BSc in Mathematics at the University of Edinburgh. My dissertation focused on convolutional Gaussian Processes, which are a beautiful method for utilising Gaussian Processes in image understanding. During my time in Edinburgh, I interned at {" "}Opteran{" "} as research engineer, and {" "}Wood Mackenzie{" "} on the product team. In my 3rd year, I went to Nanyang Technological University in Singapore. This was a wonderful experience which not only made me 10x more motivated and aspirational, but also inspired a lot of my thoughts around the UK and how to make it better. During my time at undergrad, I played football for the university.

{/* Much Before */}

Much Before

I grew up in Sheffield, a city in the North of England (also the best city in the world). As a teen, I went on {" "}Countdown{" "} and won 4 games, finishing 9th in Series 78 (and hence, just missing out on attending that years grand final).

{/* 2. Quick Facts */}

Quick Facts

  • BSc @ Edinburgh — dissertation on convolutional Gaussian processes
  • MPhil in Biotechnology @ Cambridge - dissertation on single-cell foundation models for drug discovery
  • Interests: Machine Learning, AI ∨ Biology, UK Governance, AI Safety
  • Life Enjoyer
